HEADWORD: Interstapedial
<hw>In`ter*sta*pe"di*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to a part of the columella of the
ear, between the stapes and the mediostapedial.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The interstapedial part of the
columella.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

